Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.40,0:00:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As we learned in our audio drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.02,0:00:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews returned to Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.11,0:00:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to rebuild the temple in 537 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And by 515 B.C.E., it was finally completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.49,0:00:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the city’s walls were still left in ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.08,0:00:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s time had now come to rebuild the walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.04,0:00:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and he used the faithful man Nehemiah
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.88,0:00:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the lead in this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be a massive undertaking for the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.85,0:00:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And once again, there were opposers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.81,0:00:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah told the nation of Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How could he encourage them to be joyful
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,despite all the opposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.11,0:00:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons can we learn from their example?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.82,0:00:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.82,0:00:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but here are three to think about as you watch:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.45,0:01:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What role did prayer play in helping Nehemiah
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a courageous person for Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.42,0:01:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to direct attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.21,0:01:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what schemes did the enemies employ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.38,0:01:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to oppose the work?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.80,0:01:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite setbacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.43,0:01:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what was Nehemiah’s main source of joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.93,0:01:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.14,0:01:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then, with that in mind, please sit back
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.11,0:01:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoy the following video presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.53,0:01:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}“The Joy of Jehovah Is Your Stronghold.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.21,0:01:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a privilege to have a share
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.25,0:01:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the restoration of Jehovah’s worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.71,0:01:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People know we rebuilt the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.55,0:01:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is so much more to the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.97,0:01:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s start at the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 20th year of King Artaxerxes Longimanus,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.69,0:02:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in Shushan the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.11,0:02:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was cupbearer to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted me with his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I was far from Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.26,0:02:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I found great joy just thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.55,0:02:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about our people there serving Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.93,0:02:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—until one day when I received a visit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.39,0:02:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,from my brother Hanani.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That visit changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going on, Hanani?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:03:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How are our people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.58,0:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The conditions are disgraceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The walls of Jerusalem are broken down,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.38,0:03:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and its gates have been burned with fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.84,0:03:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.26,0:03:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but the services are nothing but empty rituals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.10,0:03:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the people and the priests ignore God’s Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.85,0:03:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to return with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For days, my conscience plagued me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.54,0:03:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Would the king even allow me to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.96,0:03:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people had sinned
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.96,0:03:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by not keeping Jehovah’s commandments,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I felt as if I were sinning
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,by not helping them in their time of need.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.77,0:04:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I begged Jehovah to grant me success.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.57,0:04:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.37,0:04:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you so gloomy when you’re not sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.24,0:04:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be nothing but gloominess of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I not look gloomy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.25,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the place where my forefathers are buried,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.00,0:04:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,lies in ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and its gates have been consumed by fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.51,0:04:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.84,0:04:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you seeking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At once, I prayed to the God of the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.98,0:04:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If it pleases the king
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.27,0:05:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and if your servant has found favor with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,send me to Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the city where my forefathers are buried,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.32,0:05:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me rebuild it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.67,0:05:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The king gave me supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.14,0:05:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an army,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.22,0:05:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and an appointment as governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We were on our way to help rebuild Jerusalem’s walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.15,0:06:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had seen a portion of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.53,0:06:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn’t until I rose
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,by night to inspect the walls
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.37,0:06:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that I saw just how badly God’s city had been treated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe the destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The time had come
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal Jehovah’s purpose for Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I gathered the leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.80,0:07:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m told he’s Nehemiah, cupbearer to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he want from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.48,0:07:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.32,0:07:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The holy city is completely vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.16,0:07:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us rebuild the walls of Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.66,0:07:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so that this disgrace will not continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will our neighbors think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have many powerful enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.17,0:08:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Artaxerxes commissioned me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.17,0:08:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to rebuild the walls and the entire city.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.50,0:08:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you see the horsemen he sent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.80,0:08:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the timber?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.09,0:08:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, the good hand of our God was upon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one to fear, not men.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.52,0:08:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He will give us success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everyone was happy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.15,0:08:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had come to do something good
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.24,0:08:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for the people of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s what this Nehemiah is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, do you see what I’m seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we can keep the Jews under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.46,0:08:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If they rebuild it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.46,0:08:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews won’t need our land or resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That means he’s planning to rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.67,0:08:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t let him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.39,0:08:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We must act, and act together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.31,0:08:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.31,0:08:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my support.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And mine, as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.40,0:09:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go to Jerusalem to keep an eye on Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.49,0:09:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposers wanted to maintain control
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and to profit from Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.33,0:09:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They wasted little time trying to intimidate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.92,0:09:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.17,0:09:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Sanballat, governor of Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.26,0:09:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to him is Tobiah, an Ammonite official
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.26,0:09:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and landowner to many of our people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.35,0:09:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They all look up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Geshem;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s a very wealthy Arabian and close ally to Sanballat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.32,0:10:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, are you rebelling against the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.04,0:10:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The king himself gave us the authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To rebuild the city and the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.13,0:10:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To rebuild the city and the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.54,0:10:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the king expects us to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.38,0:10:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you not consult with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.42,0:10:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the governor of Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.55,0:10:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, but the king appointed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.30,0:10:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah as governor of Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So why have you not asked for our help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We worship Jehovah too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve sacrificed to him for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.06,0:10:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with sacrifices to all of your other gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.48,0:10:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is the One that will grant us success,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.77,0:10:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and we, his servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.69,0:10:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will get up and build.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.90,0:10:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No one should let his religious beliefs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,come before national unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You have neither share
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.95,0:10:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,nor claim nor memorial in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.76,0:10:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,could it be you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who is rebelling against the highest King of all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.02,0:11:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite opposition,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.06,0:11:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the people worked strenuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.06,0:11:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, these things have to go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Their struggles went far beyond building a wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.17,0:11:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah remembers brothers like Peleth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.30,0:11:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing how he dealt with personal challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.76,0:11:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthened my faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Peleth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.81,0:11:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.27,0:11:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll never finish this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.15,0:11:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s nothing but rubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At least we’re trying to make a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:11:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Always an optimist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.28,0:11:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, you’re late on your rent
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.86,0:12:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.08,0:12:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham, I’m sorry;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.08,0:12:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I need more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.00,0:12:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,With the work on the wall, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.46,0:12:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I have enough troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.17,0:12:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, if I don’t get payment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.88,0:12:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of the month,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.00,0:12:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you and your family are out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything we can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.01,0:12:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I can work it off till we get caught up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.35,0:12:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.43,0:12:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have time to work it off,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.60,0:12:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but maybe your daughter can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She can come stay with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As a slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’ll hire her to help Azubah
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—to pay off your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.86,0:12:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I’m trying to help,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.49,0:12:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don’t have many options here, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.12,0:12:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So Raham spoke to me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to hire Simcha to help Azubah in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he’ll care for her like his own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.49,0:13:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Imma, I’ve known Raham and Azubah
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.29,0:13:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,ever since I came here with Ezra.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham helped us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.29,0:13:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Our house belongs to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.38,0:13:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants our Simcha to live with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.01,0:13:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Imma, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Jehovah’s command
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.64,0:13:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that parents raise their own children?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.22,0:13:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you want her to have a better life?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.77,0:13:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I cannot agree
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:13:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to having her live apart from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even if we have to survive on gleanings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.32,0:14:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know we’ll survive at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.53,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah always takes care
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.53,0:14:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who love and obey him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Men like Peleth threw their burden on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and kept working.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat set up camp near Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep an eye on our progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.36,0:14:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.90,0:14:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.82,0:14:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.57,0:14:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s up to half its height all around the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.74,0:14:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This has gone too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, how long will it take
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.91,0:14:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to assemble an attack force?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.42,0:14:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack force?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.38,0:15:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Sanballat, an attack on the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would be an attack on the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.97,0:15:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah has authorization from Artaxerxes himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.93,0:15:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw how many horsemen the king sent with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be talking like this if those horsemen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,were still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.93,0:15:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.10,0:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind the horsemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.44,0:15:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my province!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.61,0:15:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Out here, I decide what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.44,0:15:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we need to threaten them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.99,0:15:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, you bring Samaritan troops
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.87,0:15:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and come in from this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.87,0:15:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re preparing to attack us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard them talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.58,0:15:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Have they attacked anyone yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.54,0:15:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to wait until they start killing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.67,0:15:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.60,0:15:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.81,0:15:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,post men by families at the lowest parts of the wall 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:15:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—at all the exposed places.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.98,0:16:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.11,0:16:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.44,0:16:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.57,0:16:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if we let mere threats frighten us into stopping,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.86,0:16:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,they will have achieved their goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no use. Don’t you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,These people hate what we’re doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.28,0:16:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They hate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to live and work around them like we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.45,0:16:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.83,0:16:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,where is your faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.58,0:16:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Jehovah’s will that we build this wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is really Jehovah’s will,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then why are we getting all this opposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.59,0:16:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe this isn’t the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.59,0:16:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, this work is too much for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.42,0:16:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we need a wall anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.06,0:16:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To protect Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.02,0:16:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.86,0:16:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,do not be afraid of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.15,0:16:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.20,0:16:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who is great and awe-inspiring;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.57,0:16:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and fight for your brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.62,0:16:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,your sons and daughters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,your wives and homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you hear the sound of the horn,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.34,0:17:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,gather together to where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.47,0:17:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our God will fight for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.77,0:17:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen for this signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.61,0:17:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The threats aren’t working.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The next sound they hear will be our battle cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.53,0:17:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We already spoke about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.03,0:17:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A direct attack would be seditious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, they’ve armed themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.17,0:17:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My-my lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.80,0:17:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.47,0:17:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d never get away with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.51,0:17:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you recall who commissioned Nehemiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.01,0:17:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:18:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the king of Persia, let me remind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah is setting himself up as a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.28,0:18:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend we turn the accusation of sedition
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.03,0:18:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,against Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.37,0:18:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.41,0:18:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he will beg for our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go back to Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.57,0:18:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.75,0:19:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you look like you’ve been working.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.17,0:19:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I must smell like it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.21,0:19:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.38,0:19:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.68,0:19:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, we are well on our way to completing the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is helping us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.89,0:19:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but we must not let our hands drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.10,0:19:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.81,0:19:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we will all spend the night inside Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.98,0:19:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We will take turns keeping watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.40,0:19:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani will give out assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.49,0:19:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.95,0:20:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was working hard on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.79,0:20:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were more issues to contend with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.71,0:20:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My brothers, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.30,0:20:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, we, with our sons and daughters, are many.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.76,0:20:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We need food to stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.22,0:20:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave our fields and vineyards
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.85,0:20:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and houses as security to get grain during
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the food shortage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.94,0:20:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We borrowed money
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.69,0:20:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on our fields and our vineyards to pay the king’s tribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.23,0:20:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve had to sell some of our children into slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:21:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re powerless to stop this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because our fields and vineyards belong to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.62,0:21:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for bringing this to my attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I must ponder all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani, please tell all the nobles
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.22,0:21:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and deputy rulers to come to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.18,0:21:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,first thing tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.14,0:21:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With God’s help, we can make this right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.90,0:21:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Men of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.07,0:21:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,each of you is demanding interest from your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.62,0:21:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be ashamed of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.62,0:21:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you not walk in the fear of our God
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.13,0:21:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the nations, our enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.84,0:21:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot reproach us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.21,0:22:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, please, stop this lending on interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please restore to them their fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.72,0:22:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,vineyards, olive groves, houses,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.52,0:22:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.40,0:22:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, I will restore the fields this day at sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.11,0:22:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We all will restore these things to our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.91,0:22:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Before Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.66,0:22:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,do you swear to these promises?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.66,0:22:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We do!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,May the true God shake out from his house
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.79,0:22:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,every man who does not carry out this promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.21,0:22:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.72,0:22:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Meshullam,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.35,0:22:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we must inform Tobiah about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.35,0:22:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.94,0:23:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will bless it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.53,0:23:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.54,0:23:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I bring good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.54,0:23:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.08,0:23:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.58,0:23:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We have your rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.71,0:23:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.71,0:23:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come by anytime and collect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.30,0:23:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought we—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.13,0:23:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Simcha?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.47,0:23:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll be staying with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.64,0:23:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how were you able to put it together so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.81,0:23:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah always takes care of those
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.69,0:23:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who love and obey him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.99,0:23:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since Nehemiah got here,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.99,0:23:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,things have been getting better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.51,0:24:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah thinks we’re still as young
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.51,0:24:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as when we came here with Ezra.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.55,0:24:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.55,0:24:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But now Nehemiah treats us like it all fell out of heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.81,0:24:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and we just have to pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.85,0:24:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked hard for what I have, didn’t I?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.48,0:24:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.60,0:24:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If I give back my fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.61,0:24:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what am I to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.07,0:24:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.98,0:24:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong with lending on interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.49,0:24:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You borrow, you pay with interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.49,0:24:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham, Jehovah just wants us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.49,0:24:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to treat our brothers fairly, doesn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven’t you heard a word I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.54,0:24:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I treat everyone fairly!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.83,0:24:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.84,0:24:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.80,0:24:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you talking to me like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.88,0:24:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I just feel betrayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.68,0:24:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.68,0:24:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,By the people I’ve lent money to!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.19,0:25:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.90,0:25:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Only what a wife is supposed to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.61,0:25:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a son!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.69,0:25:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If not a son, then a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.11,0:25:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot give you what Jehovah does not give us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.53,0:25:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One day,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.29,0:25:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.76,0:25:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I say we write a letter to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.84,0:25:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s see what the boy reports when he returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.85,0:25:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Sanballat.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.68,0:25:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall has no more gaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.18,0:25:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.02,0:25:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they advance so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.19,0:25:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, there’s a letter for Tobiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.50,0:26:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah is forcing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.50,0:26:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,landlords to return their fields to the original owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.09,0:26:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re running out of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.59,0:26:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.26,0:26:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell this to Nehemiah:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.56,0:26:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come, and let us set a time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.27,0:26:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet together in the Valley Plain of Ono.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.77,0:26:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re trying to lure me away from Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.86,0:26:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to do me harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.16,0:26:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, tell your master:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.16,0:26:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am engaged in a great work,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.21,0:26:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I am not able to go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.00,0:26:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why should the work stop
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.79,0:26:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,while I leave it to come to you?”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.38,0:26:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent me the same message several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.97,0:26:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time I gave them the same response.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.56,0:27:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, he has rejected your offer a fourth time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.86,0:27:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.86,0:27:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s time to implement your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.24,0:27:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.12,0:27:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,write this down:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.37,0:27:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Among the nations it has been heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.79,0:27:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“and Geshem is also saying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.83,0:27:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you and the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.63,0:27:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“are scheming to rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.88,0:27:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why you are building the wall.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.57,0:27:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.11,0:27:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Give this to Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.35,0:28:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell your master:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.35,0:28:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“None of the things you are saying have taken place.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.73,0:28:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You are making them up out of your own imagination.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.21,0:28:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.46,0:28:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re trying to frighten us into stopping the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.05,0:28:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they know that the king won’t change his decree.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.30,0:29:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But believe me, they won’t stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.58,0:29:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I pray,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.91,0:29:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthen my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.88,0:29:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.30,0:29:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.63,0:29:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall is almost complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.06,0:29:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.52,0:29:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I know a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.44,0:29:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Shemaiah, you called for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.98,0:29:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.40,0:29:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.57,0:30:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You are in great danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.91,0:30:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so am I because I know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.57,0:30:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk sense, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.32,0:30:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.70,0:30:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re coming to kill you—by night!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.29,0:30:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go into the temple and close the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.75,0:30:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Shemaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.54,0:30:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,should a man like me run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.71,0:30:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.67,0:30:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that do to the spirit of the entire nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.55,0:30:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the only safe place.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.55,0:30:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I’m not a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.80,0:30:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If I entered the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.81,0:30:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be valid reason to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.52,0:30:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.23,0:30:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That decision would be foolish, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.69,0:30:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.15,0:30:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah and Sanballat put you up to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.07,0:30:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t they, you hypocrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.20,0:30:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah remember them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.12,0:30:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of you false prophets
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.70,0:30:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,who keep trying to frighten me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.33,0:30:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.50,0:30:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.01,0:31:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.81,0:31:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We just kept working day and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.02,0:31:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we knew it,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.44,0:31:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we were finishing the very last section of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.08,0:31:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helped us to achieve the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.18,0:31:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We were tired,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.22,0:31:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but we discovered something we had lost
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.52,0:31:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.81,0:32:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, the wall is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.11,0:32:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.44,0:32:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.07,0:32:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In just 52 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.04,0:32:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, it’s from Shemaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.43,0:32:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.02,0:32:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.03,0:32:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the doors are left to be put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.90,0:32:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat, we must act quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.95,0:32:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.16,0:32:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Tobiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.87,0:32:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there’s still time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.29,0:32:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Write that letter to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.87,0:33:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.62,0:33:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.67,0:33:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,God must be helping the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.38,0:33:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.01,0:33:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll lose all control over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.06,0:33:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn’t over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.11,0:34:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Rebuilding the walls was only the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.28,0:34:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We would definitely need God’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.62,0:34:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for what was coming next.
